introduction: Guests: Timothy Snyder is a professor of history at Yale University and author of On Tyranny Graphic Edition - Twenty Lessons from the Twentieth Century. His newsletter, Thinking about - is available on Substack.; Rep. Ritchie Torres is the Democratic Congressman representing New York's 15th district who, at 25 years old, became NYC's youngest elected official and the first Afro-Latino LGBTQ member of Congress. He is currently supporting the city's efforts to aid victims of the tragic Bronx apartment fire; Bari Weiss is the Editor of the Substack newsletter Common Sense and host of the podcast Honestly with Bari Weiss.
